beta coefficients

XtXi <- solve(t(X) %% X) XtXi %% t(X) %*% y

solve(crossprod(X, X), crossprod(X, y))

=======================================

Q is an n × n orthogonal matrix R is a p × p upper triangular matrix QR <- qr(X)

To extract the matrices of the decomposition, you have to use the companion functions qr.Q() and qr.R() Q <- qr.Q(QR) R <- qr.R(QR) f <- t(Q %*% y) # y?

Solving Rb = f we use the method of backsubstitution: backsolve(R, f)

Recover coefficients

Normal Equation

X <- as.matrix(cbind(1,mtcars[,3]))
y <- as.matrix(mtcars[,"mpg"])

lm(mpg ~ disp, data = mtcars)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = mpg ~ disp, data = mtcars)
## 
## Coefficients:
## (Intercept)         disp  
##    29.59985     -0.04122
beta <- solve(t(X) %*% X) %*% t(X) %*% y

QR Decomposition

QR <- qr(X)

Q <- qr.Q(QR)
R <- qr.R(QR)
f <- t(Q) %*% y
backsolve(R, f)
##             [,1]
## [1,] 29.59985476
## [2,] -0.04121512

Solve function

solve(t(X) %*% X, t(X) %*% y )
##             [,1]
## [1,] 29.59985476
## [2,] -0.04121512
solve(R, f)
##             [,1]
